The paper discusses the complexity of determining ideal play in combinatorial games, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms and data structures for solving puzzles, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of Constraint Logic, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The paper also discusses Combinatorial Game Theory, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for solving puzzles, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
